Rating: 4
This is a wonderful basic tart recipe and has been devoured by all to whom I serve it! I like my lemony things extra tangy so use 2/3c sugar and the zest of 2 lemons like some of the other cooks. I sprinkle frozen raspberries over the base before adding the filling as well. The raspberries look pretty in the tart and I haven't bothered with caramelising sugar on the top either. I serve with creme fraiche and a drizzle of sweet syrup I make by reducing 1 c sauvignon blanc/riesling and castor sugar.

Rating: 4
Yummy! I probably shouldn't give it 4 forks since I made some changes, but I'll definitely make this again. For the crust, I made it with white whole wheat flour, chilled the crust in the freezer for 30 min, avoided the pie weights and baked a tartlet pan for about 15 min and an 8 in tart pan for about 25 min. For the tart, I decreased the sugar to 2/3 cup, changed the whipping cream to light cream and only used 1/3 cup, and used about 1 tsp of vanilla instead of vanilla bean. I used 1/2 cup lemon juice (juice of 2 lemons) and added the zest of both of the lemons. I thought results were quite delicious, as did my friends. I didn't caramelize the top, but I'll try next time.

