Rating: 4
This is an excellent tart, the brulee topping really wow the guests. I made the tart dough the day before, gathered in a ball and kept it in the fridge. The next day I let it come to room temp for 20 minutes than rolled out between two plastic sheets to get more of an uniform thickness. The dough can be hard to handle, but it's tender and crumbly, well worth the effort.

