Agree with all the reviews. A very good, easy, yet elegant desert. Perfect for Spring/Sumemr. I made this in an 11" tart pan, adding 1/4 to the quantities listed. I also placed blue berries in mine (let the crust cool a bit, add blueberries and then the filling) and it was a nice variation. One tip. Make sure you blind bake the crust for the entire time mentioned. I pulled mine out a couple minutes early and some of the crust stuck to the foil.

Rating: 4
Although I don't enjoy lemon desserts, I made this for a co-worker who does. It received RAVE reviews. I made one slight alteration, which everyone seemd to love. Halfway during the 40 minute tart baking time, I gently laid thin slices of lemon onto the top of the cooking tart, thus allowing them to cook into the top. Then, when caramelized, the whole effect made for a beautiful presentation, plus one more bit of tang (or so I was told). All in all, simple and well received.

