Rating: 4
This is the best lemon tart ever! I've made it a few times and each time had to add more water to the crust. I too found it was easier to roll out the crust rather than trying to press it into the pan. Also, a secret for the carmelized top: Melt a half-cup or more of white sugar in a saucepan. Pour it onto aluminum foil to cool. Break into pieces and use a food processor to reduce it to powder. Sprinkle it on top of the pie and it will carmelize in seconds under the broiler.

Rating: 4
I made the base the easy way. I rolled out the dough, laid it over the dish and pressed it against the sides, ensuring that the pastry was not stretched. I trimmed the edge and put it in the freezer for 30 minutes,, before baking it. No foil, no beans, a perfect result every time. On dishes with a diameter of over 14 inches I leave part of the pastry over hanging the edge until it is cooked, then trim it while it is still hot.

